{"TopicId":167132,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Maritime pack question: sub","CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-02T21:47:14Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-02T21:47:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this submarine that I\u0027m working on, and it just goes into an uncontrolable dive whenever I start diving. Any tips on how to fix this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ebantess","CreatedById":182559,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T11:55:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou will need to have your centre of lift in front of the centre of mass, this is important because it is the reason you will be able to submerge.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nFinally you will need to make your ships centre of mass close to the bottom of it, this helps prevent capsizing as well as helping you to dive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=573942256\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eoriginal text from steamcommunity.com\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T21:03:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt still dives.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-04T21:45:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223210314\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167132\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509743020\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181590\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dragonwarp\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/3/2017 at 9:03 PM, Dragonwarp said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt still dives.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps some screenshots of your fine craft will help us ascertain\u00A0 your problem.\u00A0 I suspect it\u0027s simply not balanced with too much weigh fwd, doesn\u0027t take much to make them tail or nose happy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-05T13:33:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223211122\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167132\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221509831932\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250907\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpannerMonkey(smce)\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, SpannerMonkey(smce) said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps some screenshots of your fine craft will help us ascertain\u00A0 your problem.\u00A0 I suspect it\u0027s simply not balanced with too much weigh fwd, doesn\u0027t take much to make them tail or nose happy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUhhh. . . How do I add pictures? Still new. . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-08T20:35:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNevermind. I found out what might help. Hopefully the dive computer helps.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-08T20:37:00Z\u0022 title=\u002211/08/2017 08:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Dragonwarp\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dragonwarp","CreatedById":181590,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-10T23:53:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate: the dive computer definitely helped, but did not fix it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}